{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"OrientationSensor.populateMatrix()","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/OrientationSensor/populateMatrix","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor_APIs\">Sensor APIs</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/OrientationSensor\"><code>OrientationSensor</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/OrientationSensor/quaternion\"><code>quaternion</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Methods</summary><ol><li><em><code>populateMatrix()</code></em></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor\"><code>Sensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\"><code>EventTarget</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Sensor API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AbsoluteOrientationSensor\"><code>AbsoluteOrientationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Accelerometer\"><code>Accelerometer</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AmbientLightSensor\"><code>AmbientLightSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/GravitySensor\"><code>GravitySensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Gyroscope\"><code>Gyroscope</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/LinearAccelerationSensor\"><code>LinearAccelerationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Magnetometer\"><code>Magnetometer</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/RelativeOrientationSensor\"><code>RelativeOrientationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor\"><code>Sensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SensorErrorEvent\"><code>SensorErrorEvent</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The <strong><code>populateMatrix</code></strong> method of the\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/OrientationSensor\"><code>OrientationSensor</code></a> interface populates the given target matrix with the\n  rotation matrix based on the latest sensor reading. The rotation matrix is shown\n  below.\n</p>\n<p>\n  <img src=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/OrientationSensor/populateMatrix/quaternion_to_rotation_matrix.png\" alt=\"The formulas used to convert the sensor's quaternion to the provided matrix.\" width=\"795\" height=\"205\" loading=\"lazy\">\n</p>\n<p>where:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>W = cos(θ/2)</li>\n  <li>X = Vx * sin(θ/2)</li>\n  <li>Y = Vy * sin(θ/2)</li>\n  <li>Z = Vz * sin(θ/2)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  If a feature policy blocks use of a feature it is because your code is inconsistent\n  with the policies set on your server. This is not something that would ever be shown to\n  a user. The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Feature-Policy\"><code>Feature-Policy</code></a> HTTP header article contains implementation\n  instructions.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js-nolint notranslate\">populateMatrix(targetMatrix)\n</pre></div>\n<p>\n  Because <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/OrientationSensor\"><code>OrientationSensor</code></a> is a base class, <code>populateMatrix</code>\n  may only be read from one of its derived classes.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"targetmatrix\"><code>targetMatrix</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>TBD</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>None (<a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/undefined\"><code>undefined</code></a>).</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token comment\">// TBD</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/orientation-sensor/#orientationsensor-populatematrix","title":"Orientation Sensor"}],"query":"api.OrientationSensor.populateMatrix"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.OrientationSensor.populateMatrix","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/OrientationSensor/populateMatrix/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The populateMatrix method of the\n  OrientationSensor interface populates the given target matrix with the\n  rotation matrix based on the latest sensor reading. The rotation matrix is shown\n  below.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-13T06:09:49.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/orientationsensor/populatematrix","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/orientationsensor/populatematrix/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/2b8f5d9a29f00aea5d2edfa78d1fb90c51752858","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/OrientationSensor","title":"OrientationSensor"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/OrientationSensor/populateMatrix","title":"OrientationSensor.populateMatrix()"}],"pageTitle":"OrientationSensor.populateMatrix() - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}